## Control Principles Embedded in This SOP

### 1) Repeatability
The close should run the same way every period.

### 2) No Surprises
Risk must be visible through status and RAG.

### 3) Evidence Matters
Every number must be supportable.

### 4) Segregation of Duties
Preparation and review are separate.

### 5) Locked Governance
Templates and processes cannot change informally.

---

## Core Activities in This SOP

### Roles & Accountability
- preparers execute  
- reviewers validate  
- management approves exceptions  

### Close Infrastructure
- locked master template  
- controlled working copy  
- assumptions framework  

### Status & RAG
- tasks move through defined stages  
- risk visibility is mandatory  

### Accuracy & Completeness
- tie to source systems  
- maintain references  
- capture sign-offs  

### Estimates & Exceptions
- must be documented  
- require approval  

### Dependencies
- must be satisfied before review  

### Post-Close
- exceptional and controlled  

### Evidence Retention
- structured storage required  

### Version Control
- changes require authorisation  

